VL  - 27
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Discrepancies in the pay expectations of male and female management students were investigated, and potential causes of such discrepancies were explored. Females were found to have significantly lower career-entry and career peak pay expectations than males. Sex differences in career paths, comparison standards, and job facet importance were identified as potentially important explanations for these sex differences.
AB  - Discrepancies in the pay expectations of male and female management students were investigated, and potential causes of such discrepancies were explored. Females were found to have significantly lower career-entry and career peak pay expectations than males. Sex differences in career paths, comparison standards, and job facet importance were identified as potentially important explanations for these sex differences.
